The evidence with the title ''by the grace of God': how workers survive on $7.25 per hour - NBC ... ' says Mar 6, 2013  ... About 3.6 million Americans were earning at or below the federal minimum wage of $ 7.25 an hour in 2012 , and those weren't all high school students  ... That 's a shade higher than the poverty threshold for a household containing two adults , and about $ 8,000 less than the poverty line for a family of four. 
